<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 11 at 2:52AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF FOG THIS MORNING...
Areas of patchy fog, some locally dense, have developed across
portions of Cameron, Willacy, and Hidalgo counties this morning. Some
visibilities have decreased to less than a mile and occasionally
as low as one-quarter mile. The fog will dissipate later this
morning.
Motorists should use low beam headlights, reduce speed, and leave
extra space when encountering fog.</description>
